        "info": {
            "species": "A Species entry is a single biological fish, invertebrate, or plant in the system catalog. It holds taxonomy (common \u0026 scientific names), water parameter requirements, behavioral profile, and searchable tags. Each species must belong to one Type.",
            "types": "Types are the top-level classification categories for species — e.g. \"Freshwater Fish\", \"Cichlid\", \"Invertebrate\", or \"Live Plant\". Every species must belong to exactly one Type. Types power the main filter on the species catalog.",
            "tags": "Tags are free-form keyword labels attached to species — e.g. \"beginner-friendly\", \"aggressive\", \"schooling\", \"planted-tank\". They drive the discovery and compatibility search engine. Keep codes short, reusable, and meaningful.",
            "rules": "Compatibility Rules define biological constraints between tagged species — e.g. predators vs. small fish. Each rule links two tags with a severity level (Info, Warning, Danger) and an explanatory message. The engine uses these rules to flag incompatible tank mates."
        },
